\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 \
Steps
\f2\b0\fs24 \
If you've ever built a Lego set, you know all about steps already. Bricksmith forces each model to have at least one step. But let's live dangerously and add some more. Go to Model
\f4 \'ae
\f2 Add Step. Now you have a brand new step to organize parts in. To see your model like a series of instructions, go to View
\f4 \'ae
\f2 Step Display.\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\li540\ql\qnatural

\f5\i \cf0 Exporting Steps: 
\f2\i0 If you go to File
\f4 \'ae
\f2 Export Steps, Bricksmith will create a series of files based on your model, each one containing one more step than the last. That's just what you'll need when doing renderings of your instructions with the POV-Ray raytracer.\
\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs26 \cf0 Becoming your own Pixar
\f2\b0\fs24 \
You can make gorgeous 3D renderings of your model. Go download the command-line utility L3P and feed it your LDraw file (L3P Launcher is a GUI front-end.) L3P produces scenes for the free raytracer POV-Ray. Just get POV-Ray, open your L3P output in it, and render. Ooo. Ahhh. More detailed instructions are available at www.ldraw.org.\
\

\f0\b\fs26 Nerds' Corner\'d1Don't read this unless you care
\f2\b0\fs24 \
For the sake of coding simplicity, Bricksmith forces some assumptions on LDraw. The biggest one is presenting the file hierarchically. All files are treated like MPD files, and all models have at least one step. The first model and first step are actually implicit. If you only have one model in your file, you don't get an MPD file when you save. Likewise, all parts that come before the first step command in the file are assumed to be part of an implicit "Step 1."\
\
Also, Bricksmith forsook several LDraw features, most notably Conditional Lines. They aren't drawn, period. That's why the display looks so awful. It's something I hope to work on. I also never got around to certain MLCad features like step-rotations.\
\

